        "source_fetched_at": "2026-02-20T19:26:06+00:00",
        "statement_id": "doc::unsafe-keyword.md::section:0001::statement:002",
        "statement_text": "Specifically: - It is used to mark code that *defines* extra safety conditions that must be upheld elsewhere. - This includes `unsafe fn`, `unsafe static`, and `unsafe trait`. - It is used to mark code that the programmer *asserts* satisfies safety conditions defined elsewhere. - This includes `unsafe {}`, `unsafe impl`, `unsafe fn` without [`unsafe_op_in_unsafe_fn`], `unsafe extern`, and `#[unsafe(attr)]`.",
        "text_sha256": "96e6dc576eceb9f88e9c84ebef5146c7746e128d5867d9a9a13102b2166ab664",
        "token_overlap_count": 0
      },
