        "source_anchor": "https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/behavior-considered-undefined.html#behavior-considered-undefined",
        "source_fetched_at": "2026-02-20T19:26:06+00:00",
        "statement_id": "doc::behavior-considered-undefined.md::section:0001::statement:003",
        "statement_text": "`unsafe` only means that avoiding undefined behavior is on the programmer; it does not change anything about the fact that Rust programs must never cause undefined behavior. r[undefined.soundness] It is the programmer's responsibility when writing `unsafe` code to ensure that any safe code interacting with the `unsafe` code cannot trigger these behaviors.",
